{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6552","heading":"Definitions","label":"6552 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch84/schIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6552","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe Act of , referred to in par. (2)(A), is , , popularly known as the Agricultural College Act of 1890 and also as the Second Morrill Act, which is classified generally to subchapter II (§ 321 et seq.) of chapter 13 of Title 7, Agriculture. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.August 30, 1890act Aug. 30, 1890, ch. 84126 Stat. 417section 321 of Title 7"],"amendments":["References in TextThe Act of , referred to in par. (2)(A), is , , popularly known as the Agricultural College Act of 1890 and also as the Second Morrill Act, which is classified generally to subchapter II (§ 321 et seq.) of chapter 13 of Title 7, Agriculture. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.August 30, 1890act Aug. 30, 1890, ch. 84126 Stat. 417section 321 of Title 7"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Applied silvicultural assessment","label":"1 Applied silvicultural assessment","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6552%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6552%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “applied silvicultural assessment” means any vegetative or other treatment carried out for information gathering and research purposes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Inclusions","label":"B Inclusions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6552%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “applied silvicultural assessment” includes timber harvesting, thinning, prescribed burning, pruning, and any combination of those activities.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"1890 Institution","label":"2 1890 Institution","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6552%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6552%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “1890 Institution” means a college or university that is eligible to receive funds under the Act of ( et seq.).August 30, 18907 U.S.C. 321","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Inclusion","label":"B Inclusion","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6552/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6552%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “1890 Institution” includes Tuskegee University.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effecti